direction-type.words: No, not despairingly come I to Thee;
No, not distrustingly bend I the knee:
Sin hath gone over me, yet is this still
Ah! mine iniquity crimson hath been,
Sin of not loving Thee, sin of not trusting
and kind art Thou when poor
is peace and light this soul within;
on Thee, my God, guided along
I walk with Thee, the loved
